   **GLOBAL FIX:**
   To prevent this class of null pointer dereference bugs in deeply nested
   pointer structures, use one of these architectural approaches:
   
   1. **Use references instead of pointers where null should never be valid:**
   ```cpp
   struct David {
     int &data;  // Cannot be null
   };
   struct Charlie {
     David &d1;  // Cannot be null
   };
   struct Bob {
     Charlie &c1;
     Charlie &c2;
     David &d2;
   };
   struct Adam {
     Bob &b1;
     Bob &b2;
   };
   ```
   
   2. **Use std::optional or smart pointers with explicit null checking:**
   ```cpp
