       return std::nullopt;
     }
     return *b2->c2->d1->data;
   }
   ```
   
   The reference-based approach (option 1) is preferred when null values are
   logically invalid, as it eliminates the possibility of null pointer
   dereferences at compile time by making the type system enforce non-
